children.name: aboutSubtitle
children.content: Ventok is a business tools and automation studio based in Tallinn, Estonia. We help companies escape spreadsheet chaos and build systems that scale.

children.name: value1Desc
children.content: We build tools shaped around your actual workflows, not someone else's best practices. Every business is different, and your tools should reflect that.

children.name: value2Desc
children.content: We believe in automation that saves real hours, not automation that just sounds impressive in meetings. If it doesn't make your team's life easier, we don't build it.

children.name: value3Desc
children.content: We'll tell you what we're going to build, and then we'll actually build it. No scope creep, no endless revisions, no surprises.

children.name: value4Desc
children.content: We don't disappear after launch. We stick around to make sure everything works in the real world and iterate based on how your team actually uses it.

children.name: faqSubtitle
children.content: Everything you need to know about working with Ventok.

children.name: answer
children.content: Ventok is a design and automation agency based in Tallinn, Estonia. We help small and medium-sized businesses replace manual processes, spreadsheets, and disconnected tools with custom internal systems, workflow automation, and integrations. We build dashboards, admin panels, and web applications tailored to how your business actually operates.

children.name: answer
children.content: Ventok works with Estonian SMEs that have outgrown spreadsheets but aren't ready for expensive enterprise software. Our typical clients are businesses with 5-50 employees who spend too much time on manual data entry, copy-pasting between systems, or managing operations in Excel. Industries include manufacturing, logistics, retail, and professional services.

children.name: answer
children.content: Ventok is based in Tallinn, Estonia. We work with clients throughout Estonia and can conduct on-site process audits in Tallinn, Tartu, and surrounding areas. Remote collaboration is also available for all project types.

children.name: question
children.content: What types of projects does Ventok do?

children.name: answer
children.content: Ventok delivers five core services: process audits to identify automation opportunities, workflow automation to eliminate repetitive tasks, system integrations to connect your existing tools, internal tools like dashboards and admin panels, and web design for business applications. Most projects combine multiple services based on your specific needs.

children.name: answer
children.content: A process audit is a structured analysis of your business operations to identify where time is wasted and where automation would have the biggest impact. We map how work actually flows through your team, find bottlenecks, and deliver a prioritized roadmap of improvements with estimated ROI. Process audits typically take 1-2 weeks.

children.name: answer
children.content: Workflow automation replaces manual, repetitive tasks with systems that run automatically. Examples include: automatically creating invoices when orders are completed, syncing inventory across multiple platforms, sending client updates without manual emails, or generating reports on a schedule. We use tools like Make, Airtable, and custom integrations.

children.name: answer
children.content: Internal tools are custom applications built specifically for your team's workflows. Unlike off-the-shelf software, they're designed around how your business actually operates. Examples include inventory management dashboards, client portals, order tracking systems, and admin panels. We build these using modern platforms that don't require ongoing developer maintenance.

children.name: question
children.content: Can you connect my existing systems?

children.name: answer
children.content: Yes. We specialize in integrating tools that don't natively talk to each other. Common integrations include: CRM to accounting software, e-commerce to inventory management, email to project management, and ERP to reporting dashboards. If your tools have an API or support Zapier/Make, we can likely connect them.

children.name: question
children.content: How does a project with Ventok work?

children.name: answer
children.content: Every project follows four phases: discovery (understanding your current processes and goals), planning (detailed proposal with scope, timeline, and cost), build (iterative development with regular check-ins), and handoff (training, documentation, and go-live support). We communicate progress weekly and involve you at key decision points.

children.name: question
children.content: How long does a typical project take?

children.name: answer
children.content: Timeline depends on complexity. Process audits take 1-2 weeks. Simple automations and integrations take 2-4 weeks. Internal tools and dashboards take 4-8 weeks. Larger system overhauls may take 2-3 months. We provide a specific timeline estimate in every proposal before work begins.

children.name: question
children.content: What do you need from me to start?

children.name: answer
children.content: To begin, we need: access to the systems you currently use (view-only is fine initially), time with the people who do the actual work (30-60 minutes for interviews), examples of your current processes (spreadsheets, documents, screenshots), and clarity on what problems you most want to solve. We guide you through everything.

children.name: question
children.content: How involved do I need to be during the project?

children.name: answer
children.content: We minimize demands on your time while keeping you informed. Expect 1-2 hours per week for check-ins and approvals during active development. More involvement is needed during discovery (process interviews) and handoff (training). We handle the technical work; you provide business context and feedback.

children.name: question
children.content: How much does a project cost?

children.name: answer
children.content: Pricing depends on scope and complexity. Process audits start at €1,500. Automation and integration projects typically range from €2,000-€8,000. Internal tools and dashboards range from €5,000-€15,000. We provide fixed-price quotes after discovery, so you know the total cost before committing.

children.name: answer
children.content: Standard terms are 50% deposit before work begins, 50% upon delivery. For larger projects (€10,000+), we can arrange milestone-based payments tied to specific deliverables. We discuss payment structure during the proposal phase.

children.name: question
children.content: Are there grants available for digitalization projects in Estonia?

children.name: answer
children.content: Yes. Estonian SMEs may qualify for EIS (Enterprise Estonia) grants that cover up to 50% of digitalization project costs. The Digitalisation Roadmap grant provides up to €10,000 for process audits and planning conducted by external advisors. Ventok can help you understand eligibility and prepare the application as part of your project.

children.name: question
children.content: Do you offer support after the project is finished?

children.name: answer
children.content: Yes. We offer optional ongoing support and maintenance packages. These include monitoring your automations, making adjustments as your business evolves, troubleshooting issues, and adding new features. Support is billed monthly or on a retainer basis, depending on your needs.

children.name: question
children.content: What if something breaks after handoff?

children.name: answer
children.content: All projects include a 30-day warranty period after delivery. During this time, we fix any bugs or issues at no additional cost. After the warranty period, fixes are covered under a support agreement or billed at our standard hourly rate.

children.name: question
children.content: Will my team need technical skills to use what you build?

children.name: answer
children.content: No. We design everything for non-technical users. Dashboards and tools come with clear interfaces, and we provide training and documentation. You shouldn't need a developer to use or maintain the systems we build. If you want to make changes yourself, we can show you how.

children.name: question
children.content: Do I own what you build for me?

children.name: answer
children.content: Yes. Upon full payment, you own all custom work created specifically for your project, including designs, automations, and documentation. We retain rights to reusable components and templates that weren't created exclusively for you. Details are in our terms and conditions.

children.name: question
children.content: What tools and platforms do you use?

children.name: answer
children.content: We select tools based on your needs, but commonly use: Airtable for databases and operational systems, Make (formerly Integromat) for workflow automation, Supabase for custom applications, React for web interfaces, and various APIs for integrations. We prefer tools that don't require ongoing developer maintenance.

children.name: question
children.content: Can you work with our existing software?

children.name: answer
children.content: Almost always. We integrate with most modern business tools including: CRM systems (HubSpot, Pipedrive, Salesforce), accounting software (Merit, e-arveldaja, Xero), e-commerce platforms (Shopify, WooCommerce), communication tools (Slack, email), and ERP systems. If your tool has an API, we can likely work with it.

children.name: question
children.content: What if we want to change things later?

children.name: answer
children.content: Systems we build are designed to be maintainable. For simple changes, we provide training so your team can handle them. For larger modifications, we offer ongoing support or project-based work. We never build "black boxes" that only we can modify.

children.content: Ventok provides digitalization and automation services, including:

children.name: item3

children.name: section2Text
children.content: Before starting, we provide a detailed proposal outlining scope, timeline, cost, and deliverables. Work begins after proposal approval. Changes after approval may result in additional costs or timeline adjustments, which will be communicated and agreed upon before proceeding.

children.name: item3b

children.name: item3c

children.name: item3d

children.name: section4Text
children.content: Projects include up to three rounds of revisions within the agreed scope. Additional revisions or out-of-scope changes are billed at our hourly rate, agreed in advance.

children.name: section5Text
children.content: To keep the project on track, you agree to:

children.name: item5a
children.content: • Provide necessary materials, data, access credentials, and inputs on time

children.name: item5b
children.content: • Respond to communications and approval requests within a reasonable timeframe

children.name: item5c
children.content: • Approve work and deliverables by agreed deadlines

children.name: section5Note
children.content: Delays caused by late client input may affect the project timeline.

children.name: section6Text
children.content: Upon full payment, you receive all final deliverables and rights to the work created for you.

children.name: item6a
children.content: • Use project visuals and anonymized case studies in our portfolio, marketing materials, and website, unless otherwise agreed in writing

children.name: item6b
children.content: • Retain ownership of any reusable components, templates, or internal tools not specifically created for the project

children.name: section7Text
children.content: If you cancel after work has begun, fees for completed work are due. The deposit is non-refundable once work starts.

children.name: section8Text
children.content: Both parties agree to keep confidential any sensitive business information shared during the project, including but not limited to: business processes, system architecture, financial data, and strategic plans.

children.name: section9Text
children.content: Post-project support and maintenance are available as a separate engagement. Terms and pricing will be agreed upon separately.

children.name: section10Text
children.content: Ventok is not liable for indirect damages, lost profits, or business interruption. Our total liability is limited to the fees paid for the specific project.
